Package fi.tuni.swdesign.group3.api

Class RoadDataParserJSON

java.lang.Object
fi.tuni.swdesign.group3.api.RoadDataParserJSON
public class RoadDataParserJSON extends Object
A class for parsing the RoadData from Json to an usable form. Generally is meant to be used with the RoadDataGetterDigiTraffic class which generates the JsonObjects needed for the functions in this class.
Author:
Aleksi Iso-Seppälä

  • Method Details

    • getRoadData

      public static RoadTrafficData getRoadData(String location, String minX, String maxX, String minY, String maxY, com.google.gson.JsonObject condition, com.google.gson.JsonObject tasks, ArrayList<com.google.gson.JsonObject> messageData)
      Returns a complete RoadTrafficData object with all the different road data information filled using the corresponding functions.

      X-coordinates must be set between 10 and 32. Y- decimals must be set between 59 and 72. Coordinates may contain decimals and are to be set in WGS84 format.

      Parameters:
      location - A string that defines the city which the coordinates belong to
      minX - A string for the minimum longitude coordinate
      maxX - A string for the maximum longitude coordinate
      minY - A string for the minimum latitude coordinate
      maxY - A string for the maximum latitude coordinate
      condition - A JsonObject for the roadCondition data
      tasks - A JsonObject for the road maintenance task data
      messageData - an ArrayList for the JsonObjects for the traffic message data
      Returns:
      A roadTrafficData object

    • readMaintenanceTaskNames

      public static ArrayList<String> readMaintenanceTaskNames(com.google.gson.JsonArray response, String textType)
      A function that goes through the maintenance tasknames jsonarray and gets all the different possible names of maintenance tasks. The JsonArray needs to be generated via the getter function getMaintenanceTaskNamesData()

      The gathered data is put to an ArrayList with the Names of the possible task names.

      Parameters:
      textType - type the parse the text to wanted format
      response - The starting point of the Json data Array
      Returns:
      An ArrayList with all the names of the maintenance tasks

    • readMaintenanceTasks

      public static HashMap<String,Integer> readMaintenanceTasks(com.google.gson.JsonObject response)
      Function that goes through all the maintenance tasks inside the JsonObject. JsonObject is generated with the getter function getMaintenanceTaskData().

      The gathered data is then put into a HashMap with the name of the task and the number of occurences of that task type.

      Parameters:
      response - The starting point of the JsonObject data
      Returns:
      A HashMap with the different task types found and the number of cases corresponding to the task type

    • readFirstCondition

      public static RoadTrafficData readFirstCondition(String location, String minX, String maxX, String minY, String maxY, com.google.gson.JsonObject response)
      A function that goes through the roadCondition data that and gets the first complete set of data from it. This includes an observation of the current condition and multiple forecasts of coming conditions.

      An object RoadTrafficData is created and the observation and forecasts are converted to usable data and put to the object with setter functions

      The inital JsonObject is to be created with corresponding getter function getRoadConditionData(). X-coordinates must be set between 10 and 32. Y- decimals must be set between 59 and 72. Coordinates may contain decimals and are to be set in WGS84 format.

      Parameters:
      location - The name of the location for which the coordinates belong to
      minX - A string for the minimum longitude coordinate
      maxX - A string for the maximum longitude coordinate
      minY - A string for the minimum latitude coordinate
      maxY - A string for the maximum latitude coordinate
      response - The JsonObject for the roadCondition data
      Returns:
      A RoadTrafficData with the correct gathered road conditions

    • readTrafficMessages

      public static int readTrafficMessages(ArrayList<com.google.gson.JsonObject> data)
      A function that gathers the total amount of traffic messages between all the different possible traffic message types. The function goes through an ArrayList containing the JsonObjects for the message types and counts the amount of messages.

      The initial ArrayList is to be created with the corresponding getter function getTrafficMessageData()

      Parameters:
      data - An ArrayList Of JsonObjects of the trafficmessage data
      Returns:
      An integer of the total amount of traffic messages found.
